1
00:00:01,769 --> 00:00:03,904
There's a fine line between love and hate.

2
00:00:04,905 --> 00:00:10,277
The pure love of a timid boy
who was bullied as a child

3
00:00:10,444 --> 00:00:15,816
has changed into furious anger and hatred.

4
00:00:16,417 --> 00:00:17,718
I won't forgive you.

5
00:00:19,253 --> 00:00:21,455
ONE YEAR LATER

6
00:00:24,091 --> 00:00:25,359
Touche, pointe!

7
00:00:26,961 --> 00:00:27,962
Prez, allez.

8
00:00:31,132 --> 00:00:33,033
Winner, Ota!

9
00:00:38,372 --> 00:00:39,240
You sure are good.

10
00:00:39,407 --> 00:00:40,307
Not at all.

11
00:00:43,778 --> 00:00:47,114
When I watch Mr. Ota,
he reminds me of Mr. Rusudo's fencing.

12
00:00:47,281 --> 00:00:50,117
Really? I think they are
totally different.

13
00:00:50,551 --> 00:00:52,253
Does Mr. Rusudo ever call you?

14
00:00:52,920 --> 00:00:54,021
No.

15
00:00:54,188 --> 00:00:57,158
It's been almost a year
since he stopped coming.

16
00:00:58,292 --> 00:00:59,293
Goodbye.

17
00:01:02,196 --> 00:01:03,931
So it's been a year already.

18
00:01:05,766 --> 00:01:07,301
According to headquarters,

19
00:01:07,968 --> 00:01:11,605
Teiko Real Estate's Shinjuku
sales area has been impacted

20
00:01:11,939 --> 00:01:15,476
by Rich Blast Real Estate by this much.

21
00:01:15,643 --> 00:01:17,478
Rich Blast Real Estate alone?

22
00:01:17,645 --> 00:01:18,512
Yes.

23
00:01:18,679 --> 00:01:19,980
That's hard to believe.

24
00:01:20,147 --> 00:01:22,349
The Shinjuku Garden Heights area

25
00:01:22,516 --> 00:01:26,887
was touted as the last holy place
in Shinjuku and was left untouched.

26
00:01:27,354 --> 00:01:30,758
That area is being bought out
by Rich Blast Real Estate as well.

27
00:01:30,925 --> 00:01:32,927
Why was it left untouched?

28
00:01:33,427 --> 00:01:36,864
The property rights were complicated.
It's hard to deal with.

29
00:01:37,465 --> 00:01:41,635
Rich Blast is offering them
way above the market value

30
00:01:41,802 --> 00:01:43,137
and pushing forward.

31
00:01:43,304 --> 00:01:47,007
Rich Blast is a foreign-affiliated
real estate company

32
00:01:47,174 --> 00:01:48,843
funded by a Shanghai financial group,

33
00:01:49,009 --> 00:01:51,345
so they are very well funded.

34
00:01:51,512 --> 00:01:52,847
Oh, the vulture fund…

35
00:01:53,013 --> 00:01:55,282
If they continue taking over
our territory,

36
00:01:55,449 --> 00:01:58,786
the Shinjuku sales office will be
taken over by the Shibuya sales office.

37
00:01:59,153 --> 00:01:59,987
What?

38
00:02:00,154 --> 00:02:03,057
-I don't mind Shibuya at all.
-Me neither.

39
00:02:03,224 --> 00:02:05,326
If we merge, then unnecessary
workers will be laid off.

40
00:02:05,659 --> 00:02:06,794
-What?
-What?

41
00:02:06,961 --> 00:02:09,864
That's why, to protect
the Shinjuku sales office,

42
00:02:10,030 --> 00:02:13,634
-I want you to work even harder.
-Yes!

43
00:02:16,403 --> 00:02:17,638
SHINJUKU GARDEN HEIGHTS

44
00:02:17,805 --> 00:02:21,008
This is Shinjuku Garden Heights.

45
00:02:22,076 --> 00:02:24,812
It doesn't look like anybody lives here.

46
00:02:25,446 --> 00:02:27,114
It's a bit lonely here.

47
00:02:28,816 --> 00:02:30,217
Chief Sangenya.

48
00:02:30,384 --> 00:02:32,319
DANDELION CLASS

49
00:02:36,357 --> 00:02:39,627
Was this a preschool?

50
00:02:41,462 --> 00:02:42,429
Chief Sangenya!

51
00:02:49,270 --> 00:02:52,406
I don't see any kids here.

52
00:02:53,507 --> 00:02:55,776
That's a beautiful woman.

53
00:02:56,443 --> 00:02:58,946
There are only seniors here. This is rare.

54
00:02:59,113 --> 00:03:01,582
Even those seniors are gone now too.

55
00:03:01,749 --> 00:03:03,083
That's right.

56
00:03:07,888 --> 00:03:09,323
Who are you?

57
00:03:10,124 --> 00:03:11,559
I'm a realtor.

58
00:03:12,826 --> 00:03:14,395
A realtor?

59
00:03:14,562 --> 00:03:16,263
We don't need a realtor.

60
00:03:16,430 --> 00:03:19,700
I'm not with Rich Blast Real Estate.

61
00:03:19,867 --> 00:03:21,435
I'm with Teiko Real Estate.

62
00:03:21,869 --> 00:03:24,204
You are still a realtor.

63
00:03:27,975 --> 00:03:30,945
A realtor will do anything for money.

64
00:03:32,646 --> 00:03:35,649
Take a look at the windows of
those buildings.

65
00:03:36,216 --> 00:03:38,752
All these windows

66
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:42,256
had a history of their own,
of different families.

67
00:03:42,423 --> 00:03:46,226
They are going to take them down
and demolish, right?

68
00:03:46,393 --> 00:03:49,263
-That is not true.
-What is not true?

69
00:03:49,897 --> 00:03:50,864
That is…

70
00:03:54,468 --> 00:03:55,970
What's the matter?

71
00:03:56,837 --> 00:03:58,806
I am nervous.

72
00:03:58,973 --> 00:04:01,275
You're nervous?

73
00:04:02,443 --> 00:04:04,545
I am not…

74
00:04:04,712 --> 00:04:06,847
trying to demolish this place.

75
00:04:07,715 --> 00:04:09,850
My job is…

76
00:04:10,017 --> 00:04:12,720
to sell… properties.

77
00:04:29,703 --> 00:04:33,173
This house has plenty of storage
and seems nice to live in.

78
00:04:33,874 --> 00:04:35,376
Thank you very much.

79
00:04:35,542 --> 00:04:38,545
It says there's something
to be disclosed here.

80
00:04:38,712 --> 00:04:44,652
That means someone either committed
suicide here or was killed, right?

81
00:04:44,818 --> 00:04:50,391
Yes, a previous resident committed
suicide five years ago in this room.

82
00:04:54,094 --> 00:04:57,498
Excuse me, my name is Togashi,
and I'm with Rich Blast Real Estate.

83
00:04:57,998 --> 00:04:59,299
We'll be taking a tour.

84
00:04:59,466 --> 00:05:02,036
Please don't just come in.
We have it reserved until two,

85
00:05:02,202 --> 00:05:04,438
so please be courteous and wait outside.

86
00:05:04,605 --> 00:05:07,775
Adachi, we won't be buying this place.

87
00:05:08,308 --> 00:05:09,843
It's a bit creepy.

88
00:05:10,444 --> 00:05:11,845
I see.

89
00:05:12,746 --> 00:05:16,150
I will look for another property
and contact you.

90
00:05:16,316 --> 00:05:17,885
-Thank you.
-Thank you.

91
00:05:19,119 --> 00:05:22,122
What do you think? Does it bother you?

92
00:05:22,623 --> 00:05:23,757
What?

93
00:05:23,924 --> 00:05:26,160
No, it's fine.

94
00:05:26,326 --> 00:05:27,961
My family business is a funeral home,

95
00:05:28,295 --> 00:05:29,563
so I'll consider it.

96
00:05:29,730 --> 00:05:31,165
Thank you very much.

97
00:05:32,499 --> 00:05:33,801
So it was Rich Blast again?

98
00:05:34,401 --> 00:05:38,205
Selling a property with an incident
to a funeral home owner is similar

99
00:05:38,372 --> 00:05:40,107
to Ms. Sangenya's selling technique.

100
00:05:40,841 --> 00:05:44,478
Sangenya did sell a home
with a history to a surgical nurse.

101
00:05:45,212 --> 00:05:47,815
A funeral home owner
and a surgical nurse are similar

102
00:05:48,215 --> 00:05:50,751
in the sense that
they are used to people's deaths.

103
00:05:50,918 --> 00:05:53,020
-We are back!
-Welcome back.

104
00:05:53,187 --> 00:05:58,292
Manager! The Western-style
two-bathroom home I was trying to sell

105
00:05:58,659 --> 00:06:00,327
was taken by Rich Blast!

106
00:06:00,661 --> 00:06:01,595
What?

107
00:06:01,762 --> 00:06:04,064
Rich Blast sold it to a big family!

108
00:06:04,231 --> 00:06:06,266
That's also Sangenya's style.

109
00:06:07,735 --> 00:06:08,936
They got me.

110
00:06:09,636 --> 00:06:10,871
Hachinohe, you too?

111
00:06:11,038 --> 00:06:13,507
What? It's Rich Blast, right?

112
00:06:13,674 --> 00:06:15,609
Yes!

113
00:06:15,776 --> 00:06:18,812
I was consulting a couple
with a shut-in daughter.

114
00:06:18,979 --> 00:06:21,548
Rich Blast swooped in,

115
00:06:21,715 --> 00:06:26,720
and they suggested a plan to let their
daughter be a shut-in forever.

116
00:06:26,887 --> 00:06:29,123
That's also Sangenya's style.

117
00:06:29,523 --> 00:06:32,993
Sangenya's methods
are clearly known to them.

118
00:06:33,594 --> 00:06:34,862
What's going on?

119
00:06:35,329 --> 00:06:38,599
At this rate, the Shinjuku
sales office may be in jeopardy.

120
00:06:40,033 --> 00:06:41,335
I'm going out!

121
00:06:43,670 --> 00:06:45,739
-Good work.
-Niwano, come with me.

122
00:06:45,906 --> 00:06:46,840
What?

123
00:06:48,108 --> 00:06:50,077
Spy on Rich Blast?

124
00:06:50,244 --> 00:06:51,178
Yes.

125
00:06:51,345 --> 00:06:53,447
How do we infiltrate to spy on them?

126
00:06:53,614 --> 00:06:55,516
We'll have to pretend to be customers.

127
00:06:55,682 --> 00:06:56,583
So we buy a house?

128
00:06:56,750 --> 00:06:58,919
Right. We're brothers, okay?

129
00:06:59,787 --> 00:07:00,888
Would siblings do that?

130
00:07:01,054 --> 00:07:02,222
Then…

131
00:07:03,290 --> 00:07:05,058
Let's say we're a gay couple.

132
00:07:05,259 --> 00:07:06,927
Oh… huh…

133
00:07:14,168 --> 00:07:15,102
Here you go.

134
00:07:18,338 --> 00:07:21,074
Wow, this is fancy.

135
00:07:22,242 --> 00:07:26,547
We are looking to buy a house together.

136
00:07:26,713 --> 00:07:28,315
Thank you very much.

137
00:07:29,049 --> 00:07:32,486
You may already know,
but our company utilizes AI

138
00:07:32,653 --> 00:07:35,222
to find the perfect property
for our clients.

139
00:07:35,923 --> 00:07:36,924
AI?

140
00:07:37,090 --> 00:07:39,626
It's artificial intelligence.

141
00:07:39,793 --> 00:07:44,031
Please answer the questions
that appear on this screen.

142
00:07:45,332 --> 00:07:47,768
I'll be back later.

143
00:07:52,639 --> 00:07:54,341
Should we try it?

144
00:07:59,012 --> 00:08:01,381
"What is your relationship?"

145
00:08:03,450 --> 00:08:05,319
We're in a relationship, right?

146
00:08:07,487 --> 00:08:09,022
LOVERS

147
00:08:10,524 --> 00:08:14,461
"Do you think a person
can understand another's feelings?"

148
00:08:15,028 --> 00:08:15,929
I do.

149
00:08:18,498 --> 00:08:22,769
"Do you think society needs drifters?"

150
00:08:23,837 --> 00:08:26,907
Why not build a palace for the drifters?

151
00:08:27,341 --> 00:08:30,477
"Who is always expected
to succeed and shine?

152
00:08:30,644 --> 00:08:33,380
A woman or a man?"

153
00:08:33,780 --> 00:08:35,949
What does it mean for a woman to shine?

154
00:08:37,985 --> 00:08:41,622
These are questions Chief Sangenya
asked when she sold properties.

155
00:08:42,122 --> 00:08:43,123
What?

156
00:08:44,157 --> 00:08:45,859
Thank you for your time.

157
00:08:46,894 --> 00:08:49,263
These five properties
are a match for you two.

158
00:08:49,930 --> 00:08:51,465
That was fast.

159
00:08:51,965 --> 00:08:53,300
Thank you very much.

160
00:08:55,836 --> 00:08:58,872
10-MINUTE WALK FROM KAGURAZAKA STATION

161
00:08:59,039 --> 00:09:01,875
These properties are all flag lots.

162
00:09:02,276 --> 00:09:05,946
Yes, how did you know that term?

163
00:09:09,983 --> 00:09:11,485
Excuse me for a moment.

164
00:09:12,853 --> 00:09:13,687
Yes?

165
00:09:15,789 --> 00:09:16,657
Certainly.

166
00:09:20,093 --> 00:09:25,666
Mr. Adachi and Mr. Niwano,
our COO, would like to see you two.

167
00:09:26,700 --> 00:09:28,435
COO?

168
00:09:32,239 --> 00:09:33,874
What is a COO?

169
00:09:34,675 --> 00:09:35,509
Look it up.

170
00:09:36,310 --> 00:09:37,511
Okay.

171
00:09:42,416 --> 00:09:44,484
Chief operating officer.

172
00:09:46,053 --> 00:09:47,220
What does that mean?

173
00:09:51,058 --> 00:09:52,859
Thank you for waiting. Please.

174
00:09:53,026 --> 00:09:53,927
Thank you.

175
00:10:07,941 --> 00:10:08,809
Sit down.

176
00:10:13,413 --> 00:10:14,581
It's been a while.

177
00:10:15,582 --> 00:10:19,753
Rich Blast's COO is you, Mr. Rusudo?
What is going on?

178
00:10:21,822 --> 00:10:22,756
That's exactly it.

179
00:10:24,891 --> 00:10:28,662
That means you are the one who
integrated Chief Sangenya's methods

180
00:10:28,829 --> 00:10:31,965
-into the AI?
-AI Machi Sangenya

181
00:10:32,399 --> 00:10:34,001
will destroy Machi Sangenya.

182
00:10:35,002 --> 00:10:36,536
Isn't that interesting?

183
00:10:37,070 --> 00:10:39,673
Kenji, you used to be so kind.
Why are you doing--

184
00:10:39,840 --> 00:10:45,579
Adachi, I'm not the same Kenji
you used to know.

185
00:10:47,848 --> 00:10:52,452
Niwano, you went to
Shinjuku Garden Heights with Sangenya?

186
00:10:55,022 --> 00:10:58,225
That ghost town area

187
00:10:58,892 --> 00:11:03,864
will be redeveloped as
a metropolitan resort by my company,

188
00:11:04,031 --> 00:11:07,100
and it will be sold to the wealthy
all over the world.

189
00:11:08,468 --> 00:11:10,070
Please don't misunderstand.

190
00:11:11,238 --> 00:11:14,541
I have no feelings whatsoever
for Sangenya.

191
00:11:17,511 --> 00:11:18,879
That's all I have to say.

192
00:11:23,950 --> 00:11:25,118
TEIKO REAL ESTATE

193
00:11:25,285 --> 00:11:27,988
Rusudo is Rich Blast's COO?

194
00:11:28,155 --> 00:11:29,056
-Yes.
-Yes.

195
00:11:29,222 --> 00:11:30,891
So that's like the vice president.

196
00:11:31,391 --> 00:11:33,760
Does Sangenya know about that?

197
00:11:34,061 --> 00:11:35,962
I don't think she knows.

198
00:11:38,198 --> 00:11:40,367
-I'm back.
-Welcome back.

199
00:11:40,534 --> 00:11:44,638
We have a problem! Rusudo is the COO
of that Rich Blast Real Estate.

200
00:11:44,805 --> 00:11:48,141
Manager, I'm going to
Yawatahama, Ehime, for business now.

201
00:11:48,575 --> 00:11:50,911
Why are you going so far away?

202
00:11:51,078 --> 00:11:54,014
It's not the time for that! Rusudo
is saying he's going to destroy you.

203
00:11:54,181 --> 00:11:55,849
That's not relevant!

204
00:11:56,016 --> 00:11:57,350
It is relevant!

205
00:11:57,517 --> 00:12:00,487
My job is to sell properties.

206
00:12:02,289 --> 00:12:04,124
-Manager.
-Yes?

207
00:12:04,291 --> 00:12:06,326
Could you give me permission
to go on this business trip?

208
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:08,095
Yes, go ahead.

209
00:12:08,528 --> 00:12:10,297
I'm off, then.

210
00:12:12,532 --> 00:12:13,467
See you later!

211
00:12:15,302 --> 00:12:18,138
What should we do?

212
00:12:20,507 --> 00:12:24,244
All we can do is sell
as many homes as we can

213
00:12:24,411 --> 00:12:27,080
while treating our clients with respect.

214
00:12:28,348 --> 00:12:29,816
That's right.

215
00:12:30,183 --> 00:12:32,219
Chief Adachi is good!

216
00:12:32,385 --> 00:12:34,888
Do walk-in sales in your area

217
00:12:35,055 --> 00:12:37,924
and see if anybody is looking
to buy a new home.

218
00:12:38,191 --> 00:12:41,228
The human-wave attack may seem outdated

219
00:12:41,661 --> 00:12:45,932
if they are using AI, but we'll use
our sincerity against them!

220
00:12:46,099 --> 00:12:47,100
Yes!

221
00:12:48,535 --> 00:12:50,203
Here you go.

222
00:12:50,971 --> 00:12:53,507
Here you go. Please.

223
00:12:53,673 --> 00:12:57,444
PRE-OWNED CONDO

224
00:12:59,279 --> 00:13:00,280
Mika?

225
00:13:00,881 --> 00:13:05,185
It takes more effort than that
to be a human billboard!

226
00:13:05,785 --> 00:13:07,087
Please!

227
00:13:08,021 --> 00:13:10,690
Do any of you want to buy a house
or sell a house?

228
00:13:10,857 --> 00:13:14,294
Please! Please! Thank you.

229
00:13:14,461 --> 00:13:16,296
Mika, that's incredible.

230
00:13:16,863 --> 00:13:18,098
Thank you.

231
00:13:18,265 --> 00:13:19,933
Not at all.

232
00:13:20,634 --> 00:13:21,701
By the way…

233
00:13:23,170 --> 00:13:25,839
this condo has a substantial trash area,

234
00:13:26,006 --> 00:13:30,177
and you can take out the trash
anytime you want. What do you think?

235
00:13:30,343 --> 00:13:32,012
Nihao. Nihao.

236
00:13:32,179 --> 00:13:34,147
I'm with Teiko Real Estate.

237
00:13:35,081 --> 00:13:36,850
What? I'm Korean.

238
00:13:39,152 --> 00:13:40,921
Would you like to buy a house?

239
00:13:41,087 --> 00:13:43,056
It'll be a great investment.

240
00:13:44,491 --> 00:13:45,492
Thank you.

241
00:13:45,892 --> 00:13:48,862
Hachinohe, you can speak Korean too?

242
00:13:49,029 --> 00:13:53,333
Yes, I can also speak Filipino
and Brunei Malay.

243
00:13:53,934 --> 00:13:56,336
I think you need to change jobs.

244
00:13:56,503 --> 00:13:58,205
Here you go!

245
00:14:00,907 --> 00:14:03,043
I can't do this! It stinks!
It's the worst!

246
00:14:03,210 --> 00:14:06,379
That's why I told you
it's not for a beginner!

247
00:14:07,113 --> 00:14:08,815
Thank you very much.

248
00:14:09,449 --> 00:14:13,086
As a token of appreciation,
please let me give you a hug.

249
00:14:14,721 --> 00:14:16,323
Please stand in line.

250
00:14:16,489 --> 00:14:18,258
Oh my! Me! Me!

251
00:14:18,425 --> 00:14:19,526
SOUTH YAWATAHAMA HARBOR

252
00:14:19,693 --> 00:14:21,361
Pop, pop, pop.

253
00:14:21,995 --> 00:14:24,464
Pop, pop, pop.

254
00:14:25,198 --> 00:14:26,466
Pop, pop.

255
00:14:37,244 --> 00:14:39,145
You are Pop Pop Hatojiro?

256
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:42,983
I am so honored to meet you.

257
00:14:46,319 --> 00:14:48,622
Everyone is desperately working,

258
00:14:48,788 --> 00:14:52,359
but the Shinjuku office will be merged
with the Shibuya office at this rate.

259
00:14:53,093 --> 00:14:56,496
I think it's fine. It's not like
they're going to kill you.

260
00:14:56,663 --> 00:14:58,932
You need to be strong enough
to accept your fate too.

261
00:14:59,366 --> 00:15:01,801
Kokoro, those are wise words!

262
00:15:05,272 --> 00:15:07,374
JO FUJIMI, NEGOTIATING
AKIRA FUJIMI, NEGOTIATING

263
00:15:08,475 --> 00:15:10,110
Two more units.

264
00:15:11,444 --> 00:15:13,213
SHINJUKU GARDEN HEIGHTS

265
00:15:13,613 --> 00:15:15,782
For Mr. Akira Fujimi's unit 603

266
00:15:15,949 --> 00:15:17,784
and Mr. Jo Fujimi's unit 602,

267
00:15:17,951 --> 00:15:22,222
we'll add another ¥5 million
and pay a total of ¥55 million.

268
00:15:23,356 --> 00:15:26,693
What are you hesitating for?

269
00:15:30,196 --> 00:15:33,566
Only you two remain
in this 130-unit condo here.

270
00:15:33,733 --> 00:15:35,669
It's time for you to let go now.

271
00:15:36,403 --> 00:15:39,439
You'll just fade away now.

272
00:15:40,040 --> 00:15:43,109
I want to fade away here.

273
00:15:43,510 --> 00:15:44,411
What?

274
00:15:45,078 --> 00:15:50,250
This… is our origin.

275
00:15:51,351 --> 00:15:52,352
Origin?

276
00:15:53,320 --> 00:15:55,855
Who are you two?

277
00:15:59,893 --> 00:16:02,529
These two are part of Magic Seven!

278
00:16:03,063 --> 00:16:04,030
Who are you?

279
00:16:04,197 --> 00:16:06,333
I'm Machi Sangenya with Teiko Real Estate.

280
00:16:06,900 --> 00:16:09,602
So you are that famous Ms. Sangenya.

281
00:16:10,270 --> 00:16:11,971
What are you here all of a sudden?

282
00:16:12,138 --> 00:16:14,974
What's wrong with you
that you don't know Magic Seven!

283
00:16:15,875 --> 00:16:17,811
I remember now!

284
00:16:17,977 --> 00:16:20,613
You are the one
who couldn't stop your hiccups!

285
00:16:20,780 --> 00:16:22,315
That won't happen today.

286
00:16:22,849 --> 00:16:26,219
You from Rich Blast,
listen with everything you've got.

287
00:16:26,386 --> 00:16:30,223
Magic Seven is a comedy magic group

288
00:16:30,390 --> 00:16:32,959
that dominated the late 1980s to 1990s.

289
00:16:33,126 --> 00:16:35,328
The members were Immortal Akira!

290
00:16:36,029 --> 00:16:39,265
This is the noble in a mask,
Jo with Sabers!

291
00:16:40,734 --> 00:16:44,637
The brothers' escape act
of the century, Hurricane Box,

292
00:16:44,804 --> 00:16:47,874
was the most popular trick of them all.

293
00:16:48,274 --> 00:16:49,743
There are seven members in total.

294
00:16:49,909 --> 00:16:51,244
During their peak 30 years ago,

295
00:16:51,411 --> 00:16:52,979
they had 14 regular TV shows.

296
00:16:53,146 --> 00:16:55,849
Especially "It's Seven O'clock!
Let's All Get Together Magic Seven,"

297
00:16:56,015 --> 00:16:58,885
was known as the monster show that had
an average rating of 42%

298
00:16:59,052 --> 00:17:01,554
and is brilliantly remembered in history.

299
00:17:02,155 --> 00:17:04,457
-You sure know the details!
-You sure know the details!

300
00:17:04,624 --> 00:17:07,127
I was your biggest fan!

301
00:17:08,595 --> 00:17:10,563
Magic Seven!

302
00:17:10,897 --> 00:17:11,965
Yeah!

303
00:17:12,932 --> 00:17:15,702
The other day, when I realized
that you were Immortal Akira

304
00:17:15,869 --> 00:17:20,673
and Jo with Sabers, I got nervous.
I apologize for that.

305
00:17:20,840 --> 00:17:23,676
Not at all. You were really cute.

306
00:17:24,077 --> 00:17:29,416
Now, could you come with me now?
I would like to show you something.

307
00:17:29,883 --> 00:17:31,317
Okay…

308
00:17:35,021 --> 00:17:36,523
This is it.

309
00:17:37,390 --> 00:17:41,060
Isn't this the preschool that shut down?

310
00:17:41,227 --> 00:17:44,397
Yes. I have a plan to restore
this preschool

311
00:17:44,564 --> 00:17:47,100
along with the rest of this complex.

312
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:49,002
The redevelopment of this is our--

313
00:17:49,169 --> 00:17:53,339
A preschool on the premises is
a dream for families with kids.

314
00:17:53,506 --> 00:17:56,276
If the childcare hours
are from 8:00 to 18:00,

315
00:17:56,443 --> 00:17:59,312
the retired seniors living in the complex
can watch the kids

316
00:17:59,479 --> 00:18:03,683
before and after
the preschool business hours.

317
00:18:03,850 --> 00:18:05,885
And if that all-generation childcare
can happen,

318
00:18:06,820 --> 00:18:09,189
it's most convenient
for families raising their kids,

319
00:18:09,355 --> 00:18:12,592
and it would provide a livelihood
for the retired seniors.

320
00:18:12,759 --> 00:18:15,361
We can bring a modern utopia to life.

321
00:18:15,628 --> 00:18:19,532
That's ridiculous.
This place was a preschool to start with.

322
00:18:19,699 --> 00:18:22,435
It closed because there were no kids.

323
00:18:22,602 --> 00:18:25,004
That's where Magic Seven comes in.

324
00:18:25,171 --> 00:18:30,276
We'll bring back Magic Seven as
a tool to restore Garden Heights.

325
00:18:30,443 --> 00:18:33,646
Nobody remembers us.

326
00:18:33,813 --> 00:18:34,848
They do remember!

327
00:18:35,648 --> 00:18:40,286
I remember, and that means
my generation will remember as well.

328
00:18:40,653 --> 00:18:45,758
Even if they do remember us,
we don't have the energy or drive…

329
00:18:45,925 --> 00:18:48,027
or talent.

330
00:18:48,461 --> 00:18:52,365
You light up whatever is left of
your energy, drive, and talent!

331
00:18:54,968 --> 00:18:59,939
Recall that charm that drove
all the kids crazy, all over Japan!

332
00:19:00,106 --> 00:19:03,910
Light up whatever is left of
your talent and shine!

333
00:19:06,479 --> 00:19:08,014
That's impossible.

334
00:19:18,157 --> 00:19:22,061
I'm Rich Blast Real Estate's COO,
Kenji Rusudo.

335
00:19:22,729 --> 00:19:26,900
I'm in charge of the redevelopment
of the Shinjuku Garden Heights area.

336
00:19:28,635 --> 00:19:33,339
Ms. Sangenya, if you are
a huge fan of Magic Seven,

337
00:19:33,506 --> 00:19:36,309
then you should know about
that past incident.

338
00:19:36,476 --> 00:19:38,378
Don't mention that.

339
00:19:39,112 --> 00:19:41,147
An incident? Do you mean this?

340
00:19:41,314 --> 00:19:45,919
An escape act by
Immortal Akira and Jo with Sabers

341
00:19:46,085 --> 00:19:48,922
caused an accident for an entertainer.

342
00:19:49,088 --> 00:19:50,323
Did someone die?

343
00:19:50,490 --> 00:19:53,159
A fingertip was a little injured.

344
00:19:53,660 --> 00:19:57,730
After that, the shows were cancelled
one after another,

345
00:19:58,231 --> 00:20:00,934
and then Magic Seven disappeared.

346
00:20:01,100 --> 00:20:01,935
That's right.

347
00:20:02,602 --> 00:20:03,803
That's when…

348
00:20:05,104 --> 00:20:07,073
Magic Seven died.

349
00:20:08,408 --> 00:20:09,642
In that case…

350
00:20:10,510 --> 00:20:13,513
there's no need for you
to cling to this place?

351
00:20:13,913 --> 00:20:16,649
We will buy it from you for ¥55 million.

352
00:20:16,816 --> 00:20:19,986
No, we'll add
another additional ¥5 million.

353
00:20:20,153 --> 00:20:23,222
We will purchase it for ¥60 million
per unit. What do you think?

354
00:20:29,062 --> 00:20:33,600
Bro, maybe this is it?

355
00:20:34,267 --> 00:20:36,302
I'm going to sell.

356
00:20:37,337 --> 00:20:38,905
-Jo.
-I'm sorry.

357
00:20:40,173 --> 00:20:46,479
If I stay here, I will never have
closure from that incident.

358
00:20:49,082 --> 00:20:53,987
I'll stay here. Even if this place gets
demolished and I die along with it.

359
00:20:54,387 --> 00:20:59,459
This is where Magic Seven was born.

360
00:21:02,061 --> 00:21:05,798
Now, Mr. Jo Fujimi, let's take care
of the paperwork over there.

361
00:21:08,034 --> 00:21:09,135
Please come this way.

362
00:21:16,209 --> 00:21:22,181
Sangenya, now this condo,
with the exception of unit 602,

363
00:21:22,882 --> 00:21:26,019
solely belongs to Rich Blast Real Estate.

364
00:21:26,786 --> 00:21:30,223
No matter how you express
your grand plan for this place,

365
00:21:30,723 --> 00:21:33,092
there is nothing you can do now.

366
00:21:33,960 --> 00:21:36,896
This is how we do it at our company.

367
00:21:37,697 --> 00:21:40,366
There is no property I can't sell.

368
00:21:42,001 --> 00:21:43,670
I wonder if that's true.

369
00:21:49,108 --> 00:21:50,743
SHINJUKU AREA

370
00:21:54,647 --> 00:21:57,216
So they took two buildings today.

371
00:21:58,284 --> 00:21:59,552
I am back.

372
00:22:00,086 --> 00:22:02,655
Where were you for several days
during this critical time?

373
00:22:02,822 --> 00:22:05,925
Yawatahama in Ehime, Shima in Mie,
Nanao in Ishikawa, Shibukawa in Gunma,

374
00:22:06,092 --> 00:22:07,593
and Monbetsu in Hokkaido.

375
00:22:07,760 --> 00:22:10,596
I got it. I got it. You've been to
several different places.

376
00:22:10,763 --> 00:22:13,099
What was that business trip for?

377
00:22:13,266 --> 00:22:16,302
Teiko Real Estate should buy back
Shinjuku Garden Heights

378
00:22:16,469 --> 00:22:18,538
which was bought out
by Rich Blast Real Estate.

379
00:22:18,705 --> 00:22:19,605
What?

380
00:22:19,772 --> 00:22:22,508
We'll buy all the units at that complex!

381
00:22:24,777 --> 00:22:25,745
What do you mean?

382
00:22:26,345 --> 00:22:29,315
We'll buy Shinjuku Garden Heights,
then resell it.

383
00:22:29,482 --> 00:22:31,284
The company won't lose anything.

384
00:22:31,451 --> 00:22:34,787
Such a thing… How much do you
think that's going to cost?

385
00:22:34,954 --> 00:22:36,689
At least ¥10 billion!

386
00:22:36,856 --> 00:22:38,324
Ten billion?

387
00:22:39,225 --> 00:22:42,995
What are you going to do
when you buy it for ¥10 billion?

388
00:22:43,563 --> 00:22:45,031
I have a vision!

389
00:22:45,498 --> 00:22:46,999
SHINJUKU GARDEN HEIGHTS
RESTORATION PROJECT

390
00:22:47,166 --> 00:22:48,735
This thing…

391
00:22:49,202 --> 00:22:50,670
is really good.

392
00:22:50,837 --> 00:22:52,171
I was touched too.

393
00:22:52,638 --> 00:22:56,743
But… I wonder what it'll be like
in reality.

394
00:22:56,909 --> 00:22:59,645
Yeah, will it be profitable or not?

395
00:22:59,812 --> 00:23:01,114
A profit…

396
00:23:03,015 --> 00:23:06,219
The real estate business
is not just about the profit.

397
00:23:08,421 --> 00:23:09,322
Manager!

398
00:23:10,223 --> 00:23:12,391
Let's believe in Sangenya!

399
00:23:15,495 --> 00:23:17,063
I believe in her too.

400
00:23:17,697 --> 00:23:18,931
You're right.

401
00:23:19,098 --> 00:23:22,802
Maybe it's a good idea
to chase this dream.

402
00:23:23,202 --> 00:23:24,504
A dream?

403
00:23:25,104 --> 00:23:26,472
All or nothing?

404
00:23:27,440 --> 00:23:28,407
I'm in too!

405
00:23:29,208 --> 00:23:30,042
Me too!

406
00:23:32,745 --> 00:23:36,983
In that case, I want
to believe in it too, but…

407
00:23:37,150 --> 00:23:39,051
Ten billion?

408
00:23:39,218 --> 00:23:42,288
How about talking to the CEO about it?

409
00:23:42,955 --> 00:23:46,826
-CEO? I've never met him before.
-Manager!

410
00:23:46,993 --> 00:23:49,095
Let's all take a chance with Ms. Sangenya!

411
00:23:49,262 --> 00:23:51,697
-Manager!
-Manager!

412
00:23:54,734 --> 00:23:57,436
Okay. I'll go see the CEO.

413
00:23:58,237 --> 00:24:00,606
I'll even get on my knees
to get that ¥10 billion!

414
00:24:00,773 --> 00:24:02,742
Yeah! Manager!

415
00:24:02,909 --> 00:24:03,910
Manager!

416
00:24:04,076 --> 00:24:07,313
-Manager!
-Manager!

417
00:24:13,085 --> 00:24:14,020
I couldn't do it.

418
00:24:15,354 --> 00:24:18,090
I was shut out
at the secretarial department.

419
00:24:18,257 --> 00:24:20,693
They were on guard, and I couldn't
even get an appointment.

420
00:24:21,160 --> 00:24:24,330
I wonder if the CEO has a policy of
not seeing his employees?

421
00:24:24,497 --> 00:24:27,934
He's the legendary realtor
who built Teiko Real Estate.

422
00:24:28,100 --> 00:24:31,170
However, no one has ever seen him.

423
00:24:31,604 --> 00:24:34,841
A legendary realtor?
That's just like Chief Sangenya.

424
00:24:36,709 --> 00:24:40,146
In that case, I will go!

425
00:24:42,048 --> 00:24:43,883
TEIKO REAL ESTATE COMPANY, HEADQUARTERS

426
00:24:46,719 --> 00:24:48,187
Thank you for waiting.

427
00:24:49,055 --> 00:24:51,090
The CEO will see you.

428
00:24:51,524 --> 00:24:52,491
Please.

429
00:24:56,028 --> 00:24:56,929
This way.

430
00:25:09,008 --> 00:25:10,409
This is special.

431
00:25:12,345 --> 00:25:14,981
What does a genius realtor like you…

432
00:25:17,016 --> 00:25:18,050
want from me?

433
00:25:18,751 --> 00:25:21,354
I am honored to have received such words

434
00:25:21,520 --> 00:25:23,856
from the original genius realtor.

435
00:25:26,325 --> 00:25:27,326
That's an exaggeration.

436
00:25:28,928 --> 00:25:31,497
I have a request today.

437
00:25:33,165 --> 00:25:37,536
Could you pay ¥10 billion
to buy Shinjuku Garden Heights

438
00:25:37,703 --> 00:25:40,573
from Rich Blast Real Estate?

439
00:25:42,875 --> 00:25:45,344
It's to save the Shinjuku sales office.

440
00:25:47,246 --> 00:25:49,482
To save the Shinjuku sales office?

441
00:25:50,049 --> 00:25:50,883
Yes.

442
00:25:52,852 --> 00:25:53,853
CEO.

443
00:25:54,387 --> 00:25:57,456
There is no property I can't sell.

444
00:26:01,961 --> 00:26:03,129
That's right.

445
00:26:07,733 --> 00:26:08,834
Fine.

446
00:26:09,602 --> 00:26:11,137
Thank you very much.

447
00:26:12,772 --> 00:26:14,040
However…

448
00:26:17,376 --> 00:26:18,711
there is one condition.

449
00:26:22,181 --> 00:26:23,816
What the hell.

450
00:26:24,717 --> 00:26:27,586
Your truck is not here yet.

451
00:26:29,055 --> 00:26:30,690
Are you sure this is what you want to do?

452
00:26:33,726 --> 00:26:36,262
-It's starting soon! Hurry!
-Let's go!

453
00:26:48,674 --> 00:26:49,742
What is that?

454
00:26:50,242 --> 00:26:51,143
Who knows?

455
00:26:54,380 --> 00:26:56,882
Thank you for waiting.

456
00:26:57,049 --> 00:27:01,454
What you will see now
is life-threatening magic.

457
00:27:01,921 --> 00:27:04,290
It's called the Hurricane Box!

458
00:27:07,626 --> 00:27:10,696
HURRICANE BOX

459
00:27:10,863 --> 00:27:13,399
The one going in the box
is a great beauty,

460
00:27:13,566 --> 00:27:15,468
the immortal Mika Shirasu!

461
00:27:16,435 --> 00:27:17,870
She's not beautiful!

462
00:27:18,037 --> 00:27:19,038
Shut up!

463
00:27:21,374 --> 00:27:25,644
Then the masked noble
who ruthlessly points his sword,

464
00:27:25,811 --> 00:27:27,646
Niwano with Sabers.

465
00:27:27,813 --> 00:27:30,549
Now Niwano with Sabers
will put five sabers

466
00:27:30,716 --> 00:27:33,519
through Mika Shirasu's body.

467
00:27:34,186 --> 00:27:36,389
What will Mika Shirasu's fate be?

468
00:27:36,555 --> 00:27:38,524
Now, Niwano with Sabers!

469
00:27:38,691 --> 00:27:39,792
Yes!

470
00:27:39,959 --> 00:27:41,861
Now, the first one!

471
00:27:42,194 --> 00:27:43,062
Yes!

472
00:27:46,599 --> 00:27:47,900
I'll do it slowly.

473
00:27:48,067 --> 00:27:49,435
This is scary.

474
00:27:49,935 --> 00:27:52,671
This is what Magic Seven did
a long time ago.

475
00:27:52,838 --> 00:27:56,342
Ah! That's right. When the last one
goes through, it jumps.

476
00:27:56,509 --> 00:27:57,643
Right, right!

477
00:27:57,810 --> 00:28:00,813
Here I go! There!

478
00:28:00,980 --> 00:28:04,850
Ouch! It went under my armpit just now!

479
00:28:05,818 --> 00:28:06,652
Second one.

480
00:28:08,954 --> 00:28:10,689
Here I go! There!

481
00:28:10,856 --> 00:28:13,492
Ouch! You are poking me!

482
00:28:13,659 --> 00:28:14,994
The third one!

483
00:28:15,161 --> 00:28:17,430
Wait! I'm going to lift my leg up,
so wait!

484
00:28:19,865 --> 00:28:20,866
The fourth one.

485
00:28:21,033 --> 00:28:22,101
Here I go! There!

486
00:28:22,268 --> 00:28:23,335
Ouch!

487
00:28:25,471 --> 00:28:26,472
Are you okay, Shirasu?

488
00:28:26,639 --> 00:28:28,974
I'm not okay!

489
00:28:32,978 --> 00:28:35,448
-Just stab her!
-Stab her! Stab her!

490
00:28:35,614 --> 00:28:38,217
Of course he can't stab me!

491
00:28:38,384 --> 00:28:39,785
What is this?

492
00:28:40,219 --> 00:28:45,191
Are you… ridiculing us?

493
00:28:45,791 --> 00:28:48,327
This is the most popular trick

494
00:28:48,494 --> 00:28:51,030
by the legendary magician group
Magic Seven.

495
00:28:51,197 --> 00:28:52,998
The most dangerous escape act
of the century,

496
00:28:53,165 --> 00:28:55,034
Hurricane Box. Is something the matter?

497
00:28:55,634 --> 00:29:00,005
This is not Hurricane Box!

498
00:29:00,406 --> 00:29:03,609
Then you show us what it is really like.

499
00:29:04,643 --> 00:29:06,545
Everything is ready.

500
00:29:09,682 --> 00:29:13,052
"The legendary Magic Seven is back!"

501
00:29:13,219 --> 00:29:15,721
Back? What is this?

502
00:29:16,222 --> 00:29:22,228
You know, you say you are
the biggest fan of Magic Seven,

503
00:29:22,394 --> 00:29:27,066
but Magic Seven is only Magic Seven
when there are seven of us.

504
00:29:27,900 --> 00:29:32,071
Please don't worry about that.
Everyone is here.

505
00:29:33,672 --> 00:29:35,441
MEETING ROOM

506
00:29:37,510 --> 00:29:40,079
Here are your Magic Seven members.

507
00:29:41,046 --> 00:29:44,950
World peace starts with him,
Pop Pop Hatojiro.

508
00:29:45,217 --> 00:29:48,888
He bends everything other than
personal will. Uchino Geller.

509
00:29:49,188 --> 00:29:51,490
An international bearer of inspiration,

510
00:29:51,657 --> 00:29:53,259
Kitaro Bankoku.

511
00:29:53,692 --> 00:29:57,062
Magic Seven's ace, Trump Torako.

512
00:29:58,030 --> 00:30:01,433
Everyone, watch your wallet! Mr. Coin.

513
00:30:02,601 --> 00:30:05,738
What's going on, everyone?

514
00:30:06,138 --> 00:30:10,042
This realtor lady convinced us.

515
00:30:10,876 --> 00:30:13,445
Everyone traveled from afar.

516
00:30:13,913 --> 00:30:17,216
Akira, Jo, so you want to go at it again?

517
00:30:17,783 --> 00:30:19,685
I got new cards!

518
00:30:20,085 --> 00:30:23,022
We heard you two will do it,
so we all gathered here.

519
00:30:23,489 --> 00:30:25,991
I can't wait to show off
my coin tricks. It's been so long!

520
00:30:27,359 --> 00:30:30,563
I'll bend a huge spoon!

521
00:30:31,063 --> 00:30:33,632
Magic Seven is back!

522
00:30:33,799 --> 00:30:35,968
We were all waiting for this day!

523
00:30:37,503 --> 00:30:39,438
-Yeah!
-Mr. Fujimi!

524
00:30:40,639 --> 00:30:43,876
Burn what's left of your talent!

525
00:30:45,077 --> 00:30:48,614
Reach heaven with the magic
of Magic Seven!

526
00:30:52,284 --> 00:30:56,088
Bro, let's go for it.

527
00:31:00,359 --> 00:31:03,762
Didn't you want to forget everything?

528
00:31:05,764 --> 00:31:07,633
I want to fire it up now.

529
00:31:07,800 --> 00:31:11,403
You know, whatever is left of me.

530
00:31:15,574 --> 00:31:16,442
Then…

531
00:31:16,609 --> 00:31:18,611
Let's do this, Akira!

532
00:31:18,777 --> 00:31:19,845
Let's do this!

533
00:31:20,012 --> 00:31:22,147
Let's all burn it up!

534
00:31:34,760 --> 00:31:37,429
What's the matter, Ms. Sangenya?

535
00:31:38,163 --> 00:31:42,434
Teiko Real Estate purchased
Shinjuku Garden Heights for ¥10 billion.

536
00:31:42,868 --> 00:31:45,070
The contract was just signed.

537
00:31:47,806 --> 00:31:49,341
That can't be true.

538
00:31:50,943 --> 00:31:52,878
I won't let you have Shinjuku.

539
00:32:01,120 --> 00:32:02,121
Boss!

540
00:32:03,055 --> 00:32:04,423
Was there something else?

541
00:32:04,590 --> 00:32:05,891
Like I said on the phone,

542
00:32:06,058 --> 00:32:11,063
we're expecting a ¥45 billion profit
with Teiko's proposal.

543
00:32:11,397 --> 00:32:14,133
It seems to me like you're bringing
your personal feelings

544
00:32:14,300 --> 00:32:15,934
into this business deal.

545
00:32:20,706 --> 00:32:21,874
SHINJUKU GARDEN HEIGHTS

546
00:32:22,041 --> 00:32:25,244
Could you fold it faster?
There's so much more!

547
00:32:25,411 --> 00:32:27,980
The flyers are printed!

548
00:32:28,814 --> 00:32:31,417
We will see you tomorrow, then.

549
00:32:32,418 --> 00:32:34,820
TV Nichi will come and cover the story.

550
00:32:36,121 --> 00:32:39,692
The event organizers are receiving
a lot of calls too.

551
00:32:40,059 --> 00:32:44,029
I'm not sure whether this will lead
to real estate sales, though.

552
00:32:44,196 --> 00:32:48,000
It's fine. There is no property
I can't sell.

553
00:32:50,369 --> 00:32:51,403
-What?
-This is trouble.

554
00:32:51,904 --> 00:32:54,440
Shinjuku Garden Heights
is being slandered on the net.

555
00:32:54,606 --> 00:32:56,642
YOU SHOULDN'T LIVE
AT SHINJUKU GARDEN HEIGHTS

556
00:32:56,809 --> 00:32:58,610
"Shinjuku Garden Heights is dangerous."

557
00:32:58,777 --> 00:32:59,978
It's trending.

558
00:33:00,145 --> 00:33:02,047
What? What's the problem?

559
00:33:02,214 --> 00:33:03,649
They are spreading fake news.

560
00:33:04,483 --> 00:33:06,318
What is going on here?

561
00:33:07,252 --> 00:33:11,023
Weakening Teiko Real Estate
is part of standard procedure.

562
00:33:11,423 --> 00:33:14,159
But this method is…

563
00:33:14,760 --> 00:33:18,497
You are aware that this is
how this company does things.

564
00:33:23,569 --> 00:33:27,106
There is nothing to worry about.
This is actually convenient.

565
00:33:28,774 --> 00:33:32,611
Take advantage of this fake news
and spread the event at light speed!

566
00:33:33,345 --> 00:33:34,279
What do you mean?

567
00:33:34,646 --> 00:33:36,215
Take advantage of the fake news?

568
00:33:38,384 --> 00:33:39,518
I see.

569
00:33:40,152 --> 00:33:43,489
If we post, "Shinjuku Garden Heights
with explosive landmines

570
00:33:43,655 --> 00:33:48,360
will host the return of
Magic Seven," it's good advertising.

571
00:33:49,628 --> 00:33:52,664
Then I'll advertise
that Magic Seven will be at

572
00:33:52,831 --> 00:33:54,633
the "haunted Shinjuku Garden Heights"!

573
00:33:54,800 --> 00:33:59,371
Then I'll post that Magic Seven
will go wild

574
00:33:59,538 --> 00:34:02,574
at Shinjuku Garden Heights
that has "structural issues".

575
00:34:05,344 --> 00:34:09,581
Then I'll spread this
to who, where, and what?

576
00:34:11,383 --> 00:34:15,154
MAGIC SEVEN REVIVAL EVENT AT
DANGEROUS SHINJUKU GARDEN HEIGHTS

577
00:34:18,190 --> 00:34:20,225
MAGIC SEVEN TO GATHER AT
HAUNTED SHINJUKU GARDEN HEIGHTS

578
00:34:24,830 --> 00:34:27,900
The word "Magic Seven" is now trending.

579
00:34:28,066 --> 00:34:28,901
It's trending.

580
00:34:29,067 --> 00:34:30,536
TREND WORD, MAGIC SEVEN

581
00:34:37,643 --> 00:34:38,577
What?

582
00:34:40,546 --> 00:34:41,413
I got it.

583
00:34:44,883 --> 00:34:45,784
Please.

584
00:34:51,457 --> 00:34:55,694
I'm so honored that you've come,
but what do you want from me now?

585
00:34:56,862 --> 00:34:58,730
I won't lose against you.

586
00:34:59,965 --> 00:35:01,266
Is that really so?

587
00:35:02,501 --> 00:35:07,105
You wanted to transform yourself
from Dojisuke,

588
00:35:07,606 --> 00:35:10,409
and so you changed your face
and your name.

589
00:35:11,643 --> 00:35:15,080
But the person you are inside
hasn't changed.

590
00:35:17,616 --> 00:35:19,485
When you appeared before me,

591
00:35:20,118 --> 00:35:24,890
you were the kind Yoshio Sanpei
I used to know.

592
00:35:26,225 --> 00:35:28,026
That's why you could sell properties.

593
00:35:30,362 --> 00:35:34,533
However, you are different now.

594
00:35:42,274 --> 00:35:43,742
That's all I have to say.

595
00:35:45,244 --> 00:35:46,411
Goodbye.

596
00:36:10,068 --> 00:36:13,739
Wow, Magic Seven is quite impressive.

597
00:36:14,940 --> 00:36:18,477
And you're thinking that our
Machi Sangenya is impressive too.

598
00:36:18,644 --> 00:36:20,879
Well, that too.

599
00:36:23,382 --> 00:36:25,317
So many visitors!

600
00:36:25,617 --> 00:36:29,354
Welcome!

601
00:36:29,521 --> 00:36:32,424
There are no unexploded shells
at Shinjuku Garden Heights.

602
00:36:32,591 --> 00:36:34,393
Please don't be fooled
by false information.

603
00:36:34,560 --> 00:36:37,496
We have a model room to view
at Shinjuku Garden Heights.

604
00:36:37,896 --> 00:36:39,698
It has a preschool too!

605
00:36:39,865 --> 00:36:41,466
The units are all barrier free,

606
00:36:41,633 --> 00:36:45,504
so it's safe for everyone,
from kids to seniors!

607
00:36:46,438 --> 00:36:50,676
Ten more minutes till the show.
Ten more minutes till the show.

608
00:36:50,842 --> 00:36:52,144
Chief Sangenya!

609
00:36:52,311 --> 00:36:53,145
We have a problem!

610
00:36:56,048 --> 00:36:59,818
I am so sorry to do this
on the day of the show.

611
00:37:00,419 --> 00:37:03,722
We were rehearsing, and then he fell.

612
00:37:04,156 --> 00:37:06,525
When we took him to the doctors,
his bone was broken.

613
00:37:06,692 --> 00:37:10,996
I guess a leftover is a leftover.

614
00:37:11,496 --> 00:37:13,198
Don't talk like that, Jo!

615
00:37:13,365 --> 00:37:15,534
We'll make it exciting without you!

616
00:37:15,834 --> 00:37:20,672
Right! We won't do the Hurricane Box.

617
00:37:20,839 --> 00:37:21,773
No.

618
00:37:23,575 --> 00:37:25,043
-Mr. Niwano.
-Yes?

619
00:37:25,210 --> 00:37:27,546
Could you be my substitute?

620
00:37:28,914 --> 00:37:30,382
You were doing it the other day.

621
00:37:30,549 --> 00:37:31,883
But that was…

622
00:37:32,050 --> 00:37:34,386
We still have ten more minutes.
I'll teach you.

623
00:37:34,553 --> 00:37:36,455
I think that's impossible.

624
00:37:36,989 --> 00:37:38,123
I'll do it.

625
00:37:38,557 --> 00:37:39,691
What?

626
00:37:39,858 --> 00:37:42,995
There is no saber I can't use!

627
00:37:44,763 --> 00:37:46,965
Please train me!

628
00:37:56,842 --> 00:38:01,413
Magic Seven, Magic Seven, Magic Seven!

629
00:38:03,115 --> 00:38:04,850
Magic Seven!

630
00:38:15,927 --> 00:38:17,896
You will be even more surprised!

631
00:38:22,501 --> 00:38:24,536
-That was shocking!
-How did he do that?

632
00:38:24,703 --> 00:38:25,637
How did he do that?

633
00:38:27,706 --> 00:38:29,107
One hundred more times!

634
00:38:34,079 --> 00:38:36,348
I'll bend anything other than human will.

635
00:38:36,748 --> 00:38:38,750
Now, everyone, say it with me.

636
00:38:38,917 --> 00:38:41,253
Amazing!

637
00:38:41,420 --> 00:38:44,056
Amazing!

638
00:38:59,037 --> 00:39:02,107
What? You are lonely? Okay.

639
00:39:02,841 --> 00:39:06,111
Come on, friends!

640
00:39:12,884 --> 00:39:16,054
Now, this is the finale.

641
00:39:16,221 --> 00:39:18,590
This is what Magic Seven is known for.

642
00:39:19,024 --> 00:39:22,594
The escape act of the century,
the Hurricane Box!

643
00:39:28,667 --> 00:39:30,168
He will go in the box!

644
00:39:30,335 --> 00:39:33,739
The Immortal Akira.

645
00:39:37,275 --> 00:39:41,546
As you can see, he's tied with rope.

646
00:39:42,013 --> 00:39:45,550
Five sabers will pierce this box.

647
00:39:45,917 --> 00:39:48,153
With as little as a wrong move,

648
00:39:48,320 --> 00:39:51,490
Immortal Akira will be dead!

649
00:39:52,057 --> 00:39:53,825
Is it going to be okay?

650
00:39:53,992 --> 00:39:56,595
Yes, it's fine.
She's actually pretty talented.

651
00:39:56,762 --> 00:39:58,764
I'll go over there and do the voice.

652
00:39:59,231 --> 00:40:00,265
Thank you.

653
00:40:03,301 --> 00:40:04,870
Chief Sangenya, you sure are good.

654
00:40:06,872 --> 00:40:08,807
Leave it to…

655
00:40:10,242 --> 00:40:12,310
That was a hiccup, right?

656
00:40:13,678 --> 00:40:15,914
I'll bring you some water.

657
00:40:22,053 --> 00:40:25,991
The one in charge of
Immortal Akira's life is

658
00:40:26,158 --> 00:40:28,093
Jo with Sabers!

659
00:40:29,427 --> 00:40:34,366
Now, here's Jo with Sabers!

660
00:40:44,643 --> 00:40:47,145
Now, the first one!

661
00:40:47,612 --> 00:40:49,047
Prepare yourself.

662
00:40:49,648 --> 00:40:50,615
Go!

663
00:40:56,321 --> 00:40:57,522
I brought you water!

664
00:40:58,623 --> 00:40:59,457
Oh?

665
00:41:00,091 --> 00:41:01,560
That person is…

666
00:41:02,928 --> 00:41:05,030
Now, the second one!

667
00:41:09,267 --> 00:41:10,402
Go!

668
00:41:14,472 --> 00:41:17,509
Now, tap, tap, tap! The third one!

669
00:41:18,343 --> 00:41:19,211
Go!

670
00:41:19,377 --> 00:41:20,946
Maybe that's…

671
00:41:23,181 --> 00:41:25,917
The fourth one! There!

672
00:41:30,589 --> 00:41:34,059
Now, the final one!

673
00:41:34,226 --> 00:41:35,760
The fifth one!

674
00:41:38,096 --> 00:41:39,130
Go!

675
00:41:46,972 --> 00:41:52,544
As you can see, Immortal Akira
has been skewered all over.

676
00:41:53,078 --> 00:41:55,814
What is the fate of Immortal Akira?

677
00:41:56,481 --> 00:41:59,918
Boys and girls! Please cheer for Akira!

678
00:42:00,652 --> 00:42:02,454
Akira!

679
00:42:02,654 --> 00:42:04,556
Akira!

680
00:42:04,723 --> 00:42:06,324
Akira!

681
00:42:06,758 --> 00:42:08,493
Akira!

682
00:42:08,660 --> 00:42:14,099
Akira! Akira! Akira!

683
00:42:18,336 --> 00:42:20,005
Akira, go!

684
00:42:41,126 --> 00:42:43,929
Magic, Magic, Magic Seven!

685
00:42:44,462 --> 00:42:47,332
Everyone loves the magic show!

686
00:42:47,766 --> 00:42:50,869
One, two, three, four, five, six, seven!

687
00:42:51,169 --> 00:42:53,571
Let's all have fun with

688
00:42:53,738 --> 00:42:55,774
Magic Seven!

689
00:43:01,346 --> 00:43:03,248
That Jo with Sabers was…

690
00:43:03,415 --> 00:43:05,650
I know. He was practicing earlier
and hurt himself.

691
00:43:05,817 --> 00:43:09,154
So Chief Sangenya was going
to do it, but she's here.

692
00:43:09,321 --> 00:43:10,822
I have no clue what's going on!

693
00:43:45,023 --> 00:43:46,191
Kenji!

694
00:43:54,232 --> 00:43:55,433
The station is that way!

695
00:44:02,407 --> 00:44:03,341
Thank you!

696
00:44:10,248 --> 00:44:12,417
SHINJUKU GARDEN HEIGHTS RAFFLE DRAW

697
00:44:12,584 --> 00:44:14,052
Please wait a little bit longer.

698
00:44:14,219 --> 00:44:16,221
It will be your turn soon.

699
00:44:16,388 --> 00:44:17,522
Please take your time.

700
00:44:17,689 --> 00:44:19,224
-You got it!
-Congratulations!

701
00:44:19,391 --> 00:44:20,291
You got it!

702
00:44:20,825 --> 00:44:24,362
This is Shinjuku Garden Heights,
which will transform itself.

703
00:44:24,529 --> 00:44:28,366
The preschool within the complex
is called the Magic Seven Preschool.

704
00:44:28,967 --> 00:44:31,603
Magic Seven, who has miraculously
made a comeback,

705
00:44:31,770 --> 00:44:34,472
will have a magic show here every week.

706
00:44:34,873 --> 00:44:37,876
Let's talk to some people
who've applied here.

707
00:44:38,043 --> 00:44:42,280
Hello! I'm all eager to move here
this spring. I'm Mika Shirasu!

708
00:44:42,447 --> 00:44:46,017
This is Takuma, my ex-husband,
who I plan to remarry soon.

709
00:44:46,184 --> 00:44:47,786
Stop that!

710
00:44:47,952 --> 00:44:51,189
By the way, Sangenjaya,
the woman who restored this place,

711
00:44:51,356 --> 00:44:53,091
used to work for me.

712
00:44:53,258 --> 00:44:55,493
-Stop that.
-Shut up!

713
00:44:55,660 --> 00:44:58,730
Well, well, she is not as capable
as I am--

714
00:45:00,265 --> 00:45:02,300
It looks like you'll be able
to collect the ¥10 billion.

715
00:45:03,268 --> 00:45:05,403
I think we will.

716
00:45:06,171 --> 00:45:07,138
You sure are…

717
00:45:08,306 --> 00:45:09,274
Sir…

718
00:45:15,747 --> 00:45:18,817
There is no property I can't sell.

719
00:45:20,318 --> 00:45:21,352
Right?

720
00:45:24,489 --> 00:45:25,457
Yes.

721
00:45:28,026 --> 00:45:29,794
TEIKO REAL ESTATE

722
00:45:29,961 --> 00:45:30,795
REAL ESTATE BROKERAGE DIVISION

723
00:45:30,962 --> 00:45:33,131
Now, we'll start our morning meeting.

724
00:45:33,298 --> 00:45:36,301
Before we start,
I would like to formally congratulate you

725
00:45:36,468 --> 00:45:38,770
on being promoted to Director.

726
00:45:39,370 --> 00:45:41,639
-Congratulations.
-Now, now.

727
00:45:41,806 --> 00:45:44,309
The brokerage sales division
became its own department,

728
00:45:44,476 --> 00:45:46,044
so that's why I'm the director now.

729
00:45:46,211 --> 00:45:48,346
Yeah! Director Yashiro!

730
00:45:48,513 --> 00:45:50,815
Yeah! Director!

731
00:45:50,982 --> 00:45:54,085
And… Manager Adachi.

732
00:45:55,954 --> 00:45:57,655
Manager!

733
00:45:57,822 --> 00:46:00,425
Director, the CEO will be here soon.

734
00:46:00,925 --> 00:46:02,594
Right.

735
00:46:03,394 --> 00:46:04,429
Excuse me.

736
00:46:04,929 --> 00:46:06,965
The CEO is at the entrance.

737
00:46:08,600 --> 00:46:09,667
The CEO is in the elevator.

738
00:46:10,335 --> 00:46:12,570
Wow, every little detail
is reported for the CEO.

739
00:46:12,737 --> 00:46:14,606
Being CEO is serious business.

740
00:46:15,039 --> 00:46:17,075
Is he a secretary or special security?

741
00:46:17,242 --> 00:46:18,676
You're right. I wonder which one.

742
00:46:20,044 --> 00:46:23,114
The CEO is off the elevator.
The CEO will be here soon.

743
00:46:23,715 --> 00:46:24,616
Three more seconds.

744
00:46:25,049 --> 00:46:28,052
Two, one, coming in.

745
00:46:32,724 --> 00:46:36,227
I'm Teiko Real Estate's CEO and the chief
of the Shinjuku sales department.

746
00:46:36,394 --> 00:46:38,062
I'm Machi Sangenya.

747
00:46:38,496 --> 00:46:41,633
Let's continue working hard
together, everyone.

748
00:46:42,500 --> 00:46:43,735
Thank you.

749
00:46:44,402 --> 00:46:46,638
Now, everyone, please get back to work.

750
00:46:47,205 --> 00:46:48,139
Yes!

751
00:46:51,609 --> 00:46:54,145
It's a bit awkward.
I feel like I'm being watched.

752
00:46:54,312 --> 00:46:56,748
-Did you say something, Mr. Takuma?
-No!

753
00:46:57,415 --> 00:46:58,449
CEO Sangenya!

754
00:46:59,017 --> 00:47:01,119
When I'm here, please refer to me
as your chief!

755
00:47:01,553 --> 00:47:05,356
Chief Sangenya! You received
a postcard from Yoshio Sanpei.

756
00:47:05,823 --> 00:47:08,159
Yoshio Sanpei is Rusudo's real name.

757
00:47:08,326 --> 00:47:09,694
What?

758
00:47:10,495 --> 00:47:11,329
Can I read it too?

759
00:47:11,963 --> 00:47:13,164
-Of course.
-Me too.

760
00:47:13,331 --> 00:47:14,866
-Me too.
-Me too.

761
00:47:17,268 --> 00:47:19,504
Sangenya, I hope all is well.

762
00:47:19,871 --> 00:47:21,339
What is he saying that for?

763
00:47:21,506 --> 00:47:22,407
Be quiet.

764
00:47:23,074 --> 00:47:27,078
A lot has happened,
but I am grateful to you now.

765
00:47:27,779 --> 00:47:29,847
You've guided me

766
00:47:30,014 --> 00:47:32,984
to be a realtor who sells homes,
to make people happy.

767
00:47:33,418 --> 00:47:34,319
Thank you.

768
00:47:35,220 --> 00:47:39,424
Currently, I am working as a realtor
in a seaside town.

769
00:47:40,592 --> 00:47:43,394
It's called Sanpei Real Estate.

770
00:47:43,895 --> 00:47:45,430
Sanpei Real Estate?

771
00:47:45,597 --> 00:47:47,765
It's very calming.

772
00:47:48,499 --> 00:47:50,368
Who is this woman next to him?

773
00:47:50,902 --> 00:47:53,037
She's Kazuko Yamada.
We were all in the same class.

774
00:47:54,539 --> 00:47:57,475
I see. Kenji is happy now.

775
00:47:58,276 --> 00:48:01,746
Please tell everyone at Teiko Real
Estate Shinjuku office, "Hello."

776
00:48:02,180 --> 00:48:03,681
Yoshio Sanpei.

777
00:48:07,452 --> 00:48:11,689
Wow, but who'd have thought
Chief Sangenya would be our CEO?

778
00:48:11,856 --> 00:48:13,691
Chief Sangenya is incredible.

779
00:48:13,858 --> 00:48:16,628
When Sangenya went to negotiate
with the CEO directly,

780
00:48:16,794 --> 00:48:19,764
he agreed to pay on the condition
that she'd be the next CEO.

781
00:48:20,365 --> 00:48:23,468
So the previous CEO knew
that Sanchi was very capable.

782
00:48:23,635 --> 00:48:25,770
Well, the previous CEO was the one

783
00:48:25,937 --> 00:48:28,873
who recruited Sangenya
at a local real estate company.

784
00:48:29,207 --> 00:48:30,875
-Really?
-Yes.

785
00:48:31,042 --> 00:48:33,878
So Sangenya told him
that she was fine being the CEO,

786
00:48:34,045 --> 00:48:36,614
but she told him
to make me a director as well.

787
00:48:36,781 --> 00:48:40,752
So then the brokerage division became
a department and I became the director.

788
00:48:41,819 --> 00:48:46,024
My wife always does favors for me.
I'm sort of happy and pathetic.

789
00:48:46,791 --> 00:48:49,160
It's nice to have a capable wife.

790
00:48:49,927 --> 00:48:54,265
So she's a CEO, chief, and a wife.
That's a lot!

791
00:48:55,133 --> 00:48:58,236
Actually, she's going to take on
one more role.

792
00:48:59,203 --> 00:49:00,471
Huh?

793
00:49:01,606 --> 00:49:02,640
A mother.

794
00:49:04,642 --> 00:49:06,678
So we are…

795
00:49:07,478 --> 00:49:09,280
going to have a child.

796
00:49:09,447 --> 00:49:12,250
What? Good for you!

797
00:49:12,417 --> 00:49:14,552
It'll be one of the actual
Sangenya Children!

798
00:49:14,719 --> 00:49:17,055
Niwano! It's time to move on
from being one of Sangenya Children.

799
00:49:17,221 --> 00:49:18,556
I wonder if I can move on.

800
00:49:18,723 --> 00:49:20,758
Let's leave personal matters aside.

801
00:49:20,925 --> 00:49:22,560
Let's toast to Sangenya's children.

802
00:49:22,727 --> 00:49:23,728
Kokoro, you make the toast.

803
00:49:24,162 --> 00:49:25,129
What? Me?

804
00:49:25,930 --> 00:49:30,868
Let's toast to Puin!

805
00:49:31,302 --> 00:49:35,940
For the Sangenya children to be born,
"chichin pui pui puin"!

806
00:49:42,080 --> 00:49:45,016
How come no one says, "Yashiro children"?

807
00:49:45,183 --> 00:49:47,018
TEIKO REAL ESTATE, OPEN HOUSE

808
00:49:48,052 --> 00:49:49,354
I've been expecting you.

809
00:49:49,754 --> 00:49:51,889
I will be showing you
around this property today.

810
00:49:52,056 --> 00:49:54,125
I'm Machi Sangenya of Teiko Real Estate.

811
00:49:54,292 --> 00:49:56,094
MACHI SANGENYA, CEO AND CHIEF
AT SHINJUKU SALES DEPARTMENT

812
00:49:57,695 --> 00:49:58,830
You are the CEO?

813
00:49:58,996 --> 00:50:01,766
Yes, I'm the CEO

814
00:50:01,933 --> 00:50:05,536
and the chief of the Shinjuku
sales department at Teiko Real Estate.

815
00:50:06,037 --> 00:50:07,338
CEO?

816
00:50:07,505 --> 00:50:09,907
But can a CEO do sales?

817
00:50:10,341 --> 00:50:13,111
There is no property I can't sell!

818
00:50:13,277 --> 00:50:15,880
THIS DRAMA IS A FICTION
